HEADWORD: Chrismation
<hw>Chris*ma"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[LL.
<ets>chrismatio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of applying the chrism, or
consecrated oil.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q><qex>Chrismation</qex> or cross-signing with ointment, was used in
baptism.</q> <rj><qau>Jer. Taylor.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Chrismatory</ent>⟦br⟧
